<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>answer one’s calling • answer the call of nature</xh5><p> <i>answer one’s calling</i>—fulfill one’s destiny in terms of profession by doing what one has a talent for: Makeup artist Elisabeth Fry said in an interview that she “<u>answered her calling</u>” to design jewelry.</p><p> <i>answer the call of nature</i>—(euph.) go to the bathroom to relieve oneself: The locals did not have modern toilets. Mong people preferred to dig a hole in their fields to <u>answer the call of nature</u>.</p> </entry>
